<!-- class Visibility: default -->
<element name="TTokenizer">
<short>Convert string into a list of tokens</short>
<descr>
<p>Converts the input from the user, in the form  of a string, into a list 
of tokens. Each token will be a string. Minimal error checking is performed. However,
a few obvious cases that are impossible are caught, such as two decimal places
in a number.</p>
<p>A finite state machine is used to convert the characters into tokens. This allows
the minus sign to be used for negative values or as a subtraction symbol.</p>
</descr>
<errors>
<p>Throws ETokenError if an impossible token is discovered, such as two decimal
points in a number.</p>
</errors>
<seealso>
</seealso>
</element>

